Shalini Sidharthan posted a new material: Chapter 2 Assignment Answers key, few guidelines and sample drawings
This material is visible to all teachers in this class. It will be permanently deleted today.
Posted 23 Aug
Dear Students, I noticed few errors in few students' magnification calculation in your Chapter 2 based assignment. - > Please note that for magnification, you should just apply the formula, 'length of the image/actual length'. The answer that you get must be written in two decimal points For eg: 42mm/13mm = 3.2307X = 3.23X -> If you are asked to write it as nearest whole number, then 3X is the answer. -> DON'T multiply that magnification answer with 1000 (like converting into micrometer). Micrometer conversion is done ONLY for questions where you are asked to calculate the actual length (where magnification and image length is already given in the question). If you have any other doubt related to this, please call me or send a whats app message to 9562642950, tomorrow. I'm hereby uploading the answers of the Chapter 2 assignment, and two sample drawing of the banana and carrot :) Regards, Shalini Sidharthan

Yes, it is really essential. First off, you should be knowing how to manage the environment as lack of proper care (we wouldn't have to do that if we weren't destroying it in the first place) can lead to disastrous consequences. Environmental degradation of "injury" can disturb the food chain which in turn can affect not only us, but the entire world, by slowly causing organisms to die out thus depriving the earth of genetic material. We do not have the authority to seize the homes of other animals or kill them on a large scale. Knowledge of the environment is common sense, which has to be acquired, or realized. It is necessary.
